[Although there are, as yet, only a handful of cases reported, it is likely that more may well become recognized despite a rapid response by the CNE. With a short incubation period of about 6 hours, the etiology may be a preformed toxin such as an enterotoxin from _Staphylococcus aureus_ or _Clostridium perfringes_ rather than an infection with a bacterium or virus, which generally have longer incubation periods.

The Cronut (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cronut) is a croissant-doughnut pastry initially developed by Chef Dominique Ansel for Dominique Ansel Bakery in New York City and offered under the same name. A newspaper regarding the "delicacy" with a picture can be found at: http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2394583/The-perfect-mix-sweet-savory-New-cronut-burger-puts-beef-cheese-iconic-croissant-donut-hybrid.html. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/3han.]
